narratives.question_text: What knowledge, skills, and insights did you develop by taking this course?
comments: I received many valuable suggestions on my projects
I learned a lot about welding and iron work. Brent is really knowledgeable about all areas of metalworking.

narratives.question_text: What are the strengths and weaknesses of this course and how could it be improved?
comments: I learned a lot of technical skills which were great, but less about art theory than I hoped to. The class is really what you make of it (as most studio classes seem to be) and I felt like I wasn't really challenged often.
Perhaps class time was not always used terribly productively

narratives.question_text: Would you recommend this course to another student? Please explain.
comments: YES, if you like making things.
Yes! A wonderful, challenging course. Brent is an excellent professor, and I learned so much. It was such a pleasure to take this class.
If you are passionate about art and sculpture, yes. Brent can teach you a lot about how to make things and different techniques.
Although you can, you probably should not take this course unless you have some experience. Otherwise you will get little out of it.
